# Container runtime options for the interactive development container.
#
# This file belongs to your project. Riprap creates it once and never updates it,
# so options you enable here survive `copier update`. It is ordinary project
# content: commit it to share one environment with your team, or leave it
# untracked to configure a single machine.
#
# Format
#   One runtime argument per line. Blank lines, and lines whose first non-blank
#   character is "#", are ignored. An option that carries a value must occupy a
#   single line in "--name=value" form, with no space before the value:
#
#       --shm-size=8g            correct
#       --shm-size 8g            rejected: this is two arguments on one line
#
#   Launching fails with the offending line when a line is not a single argument
#   beginning with "-". Riprap passes every option through to the container
#   runtime verbatim and attaches no meaning to any of them, so consult the
#   `podman run` documentation for what an option does.
#
#   These options are applied in addition to the workspace mount, credential
#   volumes, agent configuration, and working directory, which are always present.
#
# Expose the host's NVIDIA GPUs to the container
#   Uncomment both lines below to build and run CUDA software inside the
#   development container. This requires, on the host:
#
#     - the NVIDIA driver and the NVIDIA Container Toolkit
#     - a generated CDI specification, written once with
#           sudo nvidia-ctk cdi generate --output=/etc/cdi/nvidia.yaml
#       and regenerated after a driver upgrade
#
#   The second line relaxes SELinux labelling for the container, which the
#   injected driver files require on SELinux hosts such as Fedora and RHEL. Leave
#   it commented on a host that does not enforce SELinux.
#
#   Replace "all" with a device index, for example "nvidia.com/gpu=0", to expose a
#   single GPU.
#
# --device=nvidia.com/gpu=all
# --security-opt=label=disable
